iplett)</a> ，他是第一个被诊断患有自闭症的人 (19:25)。片长：27分钟</p><p class="article__body-text"><iframe height="215" src="https://embed.acast.com/theintelligencepodcast/i-spy-meeting-ukraines-intelligence-chief" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></p><p class="article__body-text">收听： <a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/the-intelligence-from-the-economist/id1449631195">Apple 播客</a>| <a href="https://open.spotify.com/show/12zKAMNyS2GNentUzxq9QN">Spotify</a> | <a href="https://podcasts.google.com/feed/aHR0cHM6Ly9mZWVkcy5hY2FzdC5jb20vcHVibGljL3Nob3dzL2Q1NTZlYjU0LTYxNjAtNGM4NS05NWY0LTQ3ZDlmNTIxNmM0OQ">谷歌</a>|<a href="https://tunein.com/podcasts/News--Politics-Podcasts/The-Intelligence-p1186979/%20%22">调入</a></p><p class="article__body-text"><i>附加音频由“In A Different Key”提供，ina Differentkeythemovie.com</i></p><p class="article__body-text">要完全访问<i>《经济学人》</i>的印刷版、数字版和音频版，请访问<a href="https://www.economist.com/intelligenceoffer/">www.economist.com/intelligenceoffer</a>尝试免费 30 天数字订阅</p>]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 07 Jul 2023 09:48:26 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> /内容/b6i7s60dgl0e6hbfv9njts37j4svbdmp</guid><link/> https://www.economist.com/podcasts/2023/07/07/an-interview-with-kyrylo-budanov-ukraines-spymaster </item><item><title><![CDATA[Will aviators ever kick their carbon habit?]]></title><description><![CDATA[<section class="css-1ugvd2u e1y6i3a60"><style data-emotion="css j1vyw6">.css-j1vyw6 img{display:block;}.css-j1vyw6 .e16qazw92{margin-top:0.25rem;}</style><figure class="css-j1vyw6 e12yhaj20"><img alt="英国航空公司的波音 747 飞机降落在希思罗机场后，发动机发出的热量使相邻飞机的视野发生扭曲。" fetchpriority="high" width="1280" height="720" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color:transparent" sizes="(min-width: 960px) 700px, 95vw" srcset="https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=360,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230708_PDP507.jpg 360w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=384,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230708_PDP507.jpg 384w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=480,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230708_PDP507.jpg 480w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=600,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230708_PDP507.jpg 600w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=834,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230708_PDP507.jpg 834w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=960,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230708_PDP507.jpg 960w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1096,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230708_PDP507.jpg 1096w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1280,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230708_PDP507.jpg 1280w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1424,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230708_PDP507.jpg 1424w" src="https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1424,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230708_PDP507.jpg" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></figure></section><p class="article__body-text">航空业的碳排放量占年度碳排放量的 2% 以上。随着越来越多的乘客乘坐飞机，这一数字还将继续上升。但该行业为自己设定了一个雄心勃勃的目标：到 2050 年实现净零排放。</p><p class="article__body-text">在本周的播客中，主持人汤姆·李-德夫林和爱丽丝·福尔伍德询问航空公司是否真的可以走向绿色。当世界上第一架电动飞机的一次旅行因紧急着陆而结束时，汤姆发现了电池供电飞行的局限性。英国石油公司 (Air BP) 的安德烈亚·莫耶斯 (Andreea Moyes) 解释了为什么可持续航空燃料（而不是电池）将有助于解决该行业的碳问题。贝恩咨询公司的吉姆·哈里斯 (Jim Harris) 认为，廉价飞行的时代可能已经过去了。 </p><p class="article__body-text"><iframe height="215" src="https://embed.acast.com/theeconomistmoneytalks/money-talks-will-green-flying-take-off" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></p><p class="article__body-text">请访问<a href="https://www.economist.com/moneytalks/" data-tegid="s3jdjo7ltifmvd584dj833vriomahkr5">www.economist.com/moneytalks</a>订阅我们新的每周通讯，剖析市场、商业和经济的重大主题</p><p class="article__body-text">要完全访问印刷版、数字版和音频版，请订阅<i>《经济学人》</i> ： <a href="https://www.economist.com/podcastoffer/">www.economist.com/podcastoffer</a></p> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 06 Jul 2023 17:14:31 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> /内容/ctqf48qffieburkj6jkhmmaf1ntqmmo8</guid><link/